nizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"There's other cases in the library where things defined on the base class only work for some of the extended classes, so I'm not sure that's a problem. \r\n\r\nFor example on material we have `material.dithering` that only works for Lambert, Phong and Standard materials. ","created_at":"2018-12-19T10:45:13.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15449#issuecomment-448550746","id":448550746,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15449","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ0ODU1MDc0Ng==","updated_at":"2018-12-19T10:45:13.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/448550746","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/5307958?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/looeee","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUzMDc5NTg=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"looeee","type":"User","id":5307958,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"I would document `customDepthMaterial` and `customDistanceMaterial` in `Mesh.html` for now since casting shadows with points and lines is problematic, see https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7738.","created_at":"2018-12-19T10:51:26.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15449#issuecomment-448552384","id":448552384,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15449","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ0ODU1MjM4NA==","updated_at":"2018-12-20T10:10:12.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/448552384","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Actually, would you consider the thought of keeping the doc on the material, and moving the prop to the material?\r\n\r\nThe base concept is that some of the stuff is shared, while the mesh has no idea about it.\r\n```\r\nclass SomeMaterial {\r\n   fragmentMain: 'glslThatDrawsColorLight',\r\n   fragmentDepth: 'somePackingGLSL'\r\n   vertexShaderBase: 'someVertTransformation',\r\n   vertexShaderLights: 'glslForNormalsAndSuch'\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIe. \r\n\r\n```\r\nmyMesh.material = myColorMaterial\r\nmyMesh.customDepthMaterial = myCustomDepthMaterial\r\n```\r\nvs\r\n```\r\nmyColorMaterial.depth = myCustomDepth\r\nmyMesh.material = myColorMaterial\r\n```\r\nIf you're applying the same material to N meshes, you don't have to set this twice. \r\n\r\n>As far as I can see from the couple of examples where they are used, \r\n\r\nIt's possible to use it in other examples, like [displacement](https:\/\/threejs.org\/examples\/?q=displa#webgl_materials_displacementmap). If for some reason all the three.js examples had DOF, or shadows, this would have to be present in all of them. \r\n","created_at":"2018-12-19T18:13:37.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15449#issuecomment-448692706","id":448692706,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15449","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ0ODY5MjcwNg==","updated_at":"2018-12-19T18:16:18.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/448692706","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/4681282?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/pailhead","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ2ODEyODI=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"pailhead","type":"User","id":4681282,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"> Actually, would you consider the thought of keeping the doc on the material\r\n\r\nThe current API seems simpler, but I don't have any kind of strong opinion on this. \r\n\r\nHowever, the documentation is currently incorrect and confusing so if this is going to take some time to work out, we should remove the current documentation in the meantime. ","created_at":"2018-12-20T09:56:20.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15449#issuecomment-448939732","id":448939732,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15449","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ0ODkzOTczMg==","updated_at":"2018-12-20T09:56:20.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/448939732","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/5307958?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/looeee","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUzMDc5NTg=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"looeee","type":"User","id":5307958,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"I vote to change the documentation like suggested here: https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15449#issuecomment-448552384\r\n\r\nThis will reflect the current usage of both properties. I don't think the documentation should account for scenarios which are currently not supported by the renderer. Like I said before both properties make only sense for meshes. And `customDistanceMaterial` is only evaluated in context of `PointLights`.","created_at":"2018-12-20T10:02:29.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15449#issuecomment-448941676","id":448941676,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15449","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ0ODk0MTY3Ng==","updated_at":"2018-12-20T10:11:48.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/448941676","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"I think it's okay to put it on `Object3D` and mention that only affects `Mesh`.","created_at":"2018-12-28T22:08:05.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15449#issuecomment-450434996","id":450434996,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15449","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1MDQzNDk5Ng==","updated_at":"2018-12-28T22:08:05.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.